$$

#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
A solution to the following problem:
https://leetcode.com/problems/solution-to-bills-and-tips/
"""

from collections import Counter

input = open("input_data.txt").read()
items = input.splitlines()
costs = Counter()
for item in items:
    name, amount, unit = item.split()
    costs[name] += amount

print(costs)

costs_by_type = Counter()
total_amount = 0
for item in costs:
    types = item.split(":")
    if types[1] == "bills":
        bills_amount = costs[types[0]]
        bills = costs_by_type[types[0]]  # type "type" is a string
        for bill in bills:
            if bill == "smoke":
                bill_type = "Smoking"
            else:
                bill_type += " " + bill
            amount_for_each_bill = bills_amount / len(bills)    # calculate amount for each bill
            total_amount += (amount_for_each_bil * bills_amount)  # total all the amounts
        for i in range(1,len(bills)):
            if bills[i] == "shake hands":
                continue
            bill_type += " "+bills[i]+ " "
        for bill in bill_type:
            if bill_type in costs_by_type:
                costs_by_type += 1
    elif len(types) > 2 and types[1] == "% TIP":
        total_amount += costs[types[0]].upper()

print(f"Amount needed per person: ${total_amount:.2f} $")
